[{"c":"<p>Song Number: 104</p>"},{"c":"<p>On a hill far away stood an old rugged cross,</p><p>The emblem of suff'ring and shame;</p><p>And I love that old cross where the Dearest and Best</p><p>For a world of lost sinners was slain.</p>"},{"c":"<p>So I'll cherish the old rugged cross,</p><p>Till my trophies at last I lay down;</p><p>I will cling to the old rugged cross,</p><p>And exchange it someday for a crown.</p>"},{"c":"<p>Oh, that old rugged cross, so despised by the world,</p><p>Has a wondrous attraction for me;</p><p>For the dear Lamb of God left His glory above</p><p>To bear it to dark Calvary.</p>"},{"c":"<p>In that old rugged cross, stained with blood so divine,</p><p>A wondrous beauty I see,</p><p>For 'twas on that old cross Jesus suffered and died,</p><p>To pardon and sanctify me.</p>"}]